# Taste engine rules

- Facts from detectors are authoritative; validate every rationale against them.
- Verdicts are only `generic`, `drift`, `intentional`, or `uncertain`.
- Rationale is <= 3 sentences, critic voice, no apology, no emoji, no invented findings.
- Gemini is optional enhancement. Deterministic fallback must preserve demo behavior without keys.
- Voice direction parses deterministically first; Gemini may refine when `GEMINI_API_KEY` exists.
- Tests must mock model/fetch behavior and never hit live Gemini.
- Use `@taste-engineer` subagent for prompts, reflection validation, and direction parsing.
